\[
\textbf{Corrected Step:}\quad \text{Since } \frac{|\cos\frac{n\pi}{3}|}{n} \leq \frac{1}{n} \text{ and } \sum_{n=1}^\infty \frac{1}{n} \text{ diverges, the Comparison Test does not establish absolute convergence. Instead, applying Dirichlet's Test—because the partial sums of } \cos\frac{n\pi}{3} \text{ are bounded and } \frac{1}{n} \text{ is monotonically decreasing to }0 \text{—shows that } \sum_{n=1}^\infty \frac{\cos\frac{n\pi}{3}}{n} \text{ converges conditionally.}
\]

